04:08.614 --> 04:12.403
[Water drips]

04:12.404 --> 04:15.444
♪♪

04:17.314 --> 04:20.153
[Water drips]

04:20.154 --> 04:21.654
- [Exhales sharply]
- [Razor clatters]

04:21.656 --> 04:23.903
[Train wheels rattling,
brakes squealing in distance]

04:23.904 --> 04:25.524
[Exhales sharply]

04:35.234 --> 04:36.813
[Rumbling]

04:36.814 --> 04:38.194
[Squeak]

04:42.154 --> 04:43.443
[Clatters]

04:43.444 --> 04:46.444
♪♪

04:56.944 --> 04:58.403
[Squish]

04:58.404 --> 05:01.694
♪♪

05:05.524 --> 05:09.693
♪♪

05:09.874 --> 05:12.533
This will certainly make me think twice

05:12.534 --> 05:14.493
about wearing my necktie again.

05:14.494 --> 05:15.873
How did you get this?

05:15.874 --> 05:17.663
Ann Rutledge left it in my bathroom.

05:17.664 --> 05:20.413
I thought I warned you about her.

05:20.414 --> 05:22.533
I made a mistake. I dropped my guard.

05:22.534 --> 05:23.953
She used me.

05:23.954 --> 05:25.833
Used you? How?

05:25.834 --> 05:27.743
To kill Troy Hendrie.

05:27.744 --> 05:31.533
Are you saying you're somehow
responsible for his death?

05:31.534 --> 05:32.913
It's complicated.

05:32.914 --> 05:37.493
Son, I know we've lost
touch through the years,

05:37.494 --> 05:39.493
but even I can see you're a mess.

05:39.494 --> 05:41.413
Why? What's troubling you?

05:41.414 --> 05:43.993
You'll think that it's crazy, that...
that I'm crazy.

05:43.994 --> 05:48.834
Nothing surprises me anymore.
What exactly did Ann tell you?

05:54.664 --> 05:58.834
I'm the Antichrist prophesied
in the Book of Revelation.

06:01.874 --> 06:04.583
[Laughing]

06:04.584 --> 06:05.913
I'm not making this up.

06:05.914 --> 06:10.663
I know Ann is... challenging,
to say the least,

06:10.664 --> 06:13.743
but this takes batshit crazy
to a whole other level.

06:13.744 --> 06:16.623
Forget about her. I'm worried about you.

06:16.624 --> 06:19.793
You need some help. Please see someone.

06:19.794 --> 06:23.033
Lean on me all you want.

06:23.034 --> 06:26.834
And whatever you do, stay
far away from that woman.

06:33.414 --> 06:36.494
♪♪

06:41.874 --> 06:43.743
[Indistinct conversations]

06:43.744 --> 06:47.704
[Telephone rings in distance]

06:51.744 --> 06:53.374
[Static hisses]

06:58.624 --> 07:00.833
[Static hisses]

07:00.834 --> 07:02.874
<i>[Roars]</i>

07:10.584 --> 07:11.833
[Door opens]

07:11.834 --> 07:12.994
- Yo.
- [Door closes]

07:12.997 --> 07:14.413
Perfect timing.

07:14.414 --> 07:15.833
You went shopping without me?

07:15.834 --> 07:18.493
Got you some fresh batteries.

07:18.494 --> 07:20.663
You know you don't have to
keep checking up on me.

07:20.664 --> 07:22.373
I'm not. I got some news.

07:22.374 --> 07:23.743
[Sighs]

07:23.744 --> 07:25.623
Collodion Collective
wants to meet with you.

07:25.624 --> 07:27.703
The photography co-op?

07:27.704 --> 07:29.663
Yeah. I sent them your portfolio.

07:29.664 --> 07:31.663
You know I'm not much of a joiner.

07:31.664 --> 07:33.533
I know, but hear me out.

07:33.534 --> 07:36.533
With editors, right, even Ceci,
we've always been on a leash,

07:36.534 --> 07:37.873
beholden to their corporate interests.

07:37.874 --> 07:39.373
Comes with the territory.

07:39.374 --> 07:40.993
Well, the Collective
is photographer-owned.

07:40.994 --> 07:42.663
It's completely autonomous.

07:42.664 --> 07:44.413
They <i> want</i> your point of view.

07:44.414 --> 07:46.083
If they let you in, you
broaden your reach by a mile.

07:46.084 --> 07:47.743
<i>If</i> they let me in?

07:47.744 --> 07:50.493
Yeah, well, they have to
approve of you in person.

07:50.494 --> 07:52.664
I can't do a dog and pony
show right now, Amani.

07:56.624 --> 07:58.793
Come on, man.

07:58.794 --> 08:00.413
You can use the win right about now.

08:00.414 --> 08:02.494
[Knock on door]

08:05.454 --> 08:06.994
[Whistles]

08:08.454 --> 08:09.833
[Door creaks]

08:09.834 --> 08:11.413
Detective Shay. From the other night?

08:11.414 --> 08:14.033
I remember. What can I help you with?

08:14.034 --> 08:16.033
I just wanted to come by, check on you,

08:16.034 --> 08:17.624
- make sure you're all right.
- [Door closes]

08:17.627 --> 08:18.729
I'm fine.

08:18.730 --> 08:19.833
Good.

08:19.834 --> 08:21.123
I heard about the thing
in the subway last night.

08:21.124 --> 08:22.663
It's a good thing you weren't killed.

08:22.664 --> 08:24.743
It looks like I should
be asking about you.

08:24.744 --> 08:26.663
Yeah, do you know, there <i> was</i> someone

08:26.664 --> 08:28.059
killed in the subway, though.

08:28.060 --> 08:29.453
Yeah, and he heard about that

08:29.454 --> 08:31.123
after he pulled the kid
off the train tracks.

08:31.124 --> 08:33.332
Saved his life.

08:33.333 --> 08:34.583
Who are you?

08:35.994 --> 08:37.413
A friend.

08:37.414 --> 08:38.873
Do you have a name?

08:38.874 --> 08:40.832
What can I do for you, Detective?

08:40.833 --> 08:42.832
Well, I got a whole bunch of questions

08:42.833 --> 08:45.533
about the, uh, taxicab incident
that you were involved with.

08:45.534 --> 08:47.623
And I have some information
about your assailant.

08:47.624 --> 08:49.583
I thought maybe you could
come down to the station,

08:49.584 --> 08:50.793
we could talk about it.

08:50.794 --> 08:52.794
Shouldn't take too long.

08:53.994 --> 08:55.743
Whatever I can do to help.

08:55.744 --> 08:57.873
I'll catch up with you later.

08:57.874 --> 09:00.664
AMANI: Sure thing.

09:03.494 --> 09:05.413
You got some big balls,

09:05.414 --> 09:07.623
pulling that kid off
the tracks like that.

09:07.624 --> 09:10.413
I just did what anyone else would've.

09:10.414 --> 09:11.474
Yeah, well...

09:11.475 --> 09:12.533
[Coins jangle]

09:12.534 --> 09:14.833
...most people, they'd like
to think they'd be the hero.

09:14.834 --> 09:17.123
But in that moment of truth,

09:17.124 --> 09:19.623
they're more concerned about
saving their own skin.

09:19.624 --> 09:21.743
It's a shame about that
other guy, though.

09:21.744 --> 09:24.493
[Coin clinks]

09:24.494 --> 09:26.033
What happened?

09:26.034 --> 09:28.993
Well, some guy got his tie
stuck in the escalator.

09:28.994 --> 09:30.244
Couldn't yank it free.

09:30.245 --> 09:31.493
[Coin clinks]

09:31.494 --> 09:33.663
Pulled his face right
into the machinery.

09:33.664 --> 09:35.833
Ripped it wide open.

09:35.834 --> 09:37.833
[Coin clinks]

09:37.834 --> 09:41.833
You want anything? Corn chips?
Twizzlers?

09:41.834 --> 09:43.413
Mm.

09:43.414 --> 09:45.163
[Beeps]

09:45.164 --> 09:48.913
[Whirring]

09:48.914 --> 09:52.413
[Flap thuds]

09:52.414 --> 09:54.333
Yeah, broke his teeth...

09:54.334 --> 09:55.874
- [Plastic bag crinkling]
- ...chewed off his nose...

09:55.877 --> 10:00.033
[Sighs] ...severed his carotid artery.

10:00.034 --> 10:03.453
Blood everywhere. It was a mess.

10:03.454 --> 10:05.333
You know...

10:05.334 --> 10:07.664
it was right about that
time you saved that kid.

10:09.374 --> 10:11.793
I saw some of the commotion.

10:11.794 --> 10:14.123
Mm.

10:14.124 --> 10:16.083
How'd you know him?

10:16.084 --> 10:17.703
Who?

10:17.704 --> 10:18.913
Escalator guy.

10:18.914 --> 10:21.034
I didn't know him.

10:22.334 --> 10:24.743
Troy Hendrie. Wall Street player.

10:24.744 --> 10:26.704
Armitage Global. Mm?

10:29.414 --> 10:31.703
I pulled the security tapes
in the subway station.

10:31.704 --> 10:33.794
It was pretty clear
you were chasing him.

10:35.084 --> 10:36.953
I was just running to catch the train.

10:36.954 --> 10:42.453
Oh, yeah? What train?
Where were you going?

10:42.454 --> 10:47.533
I'd really like to help you, but
I just don't know anything.

10:47.534 --> 10:50.373
See, here's what I'm struggling with.

10:50.374 --> 10:53.493
In the last few days, you've
been in very close proximity

10:53.494 --> 10:56.663
to a few, uh... oh, I don't
know, what do I call 'em?

10:56.664 --> 10:59.373
Unexplained deaths?

10:59.374 --> 11:01.373
Four, to be exact.

11:01.374 --> 11:04.664
And that's a shitload of
wrong place, wrong time.

11:05.834 --> 11:08.873
So... why don't you sit down?

11:08.874 --> 11:11.124
We have a lot to talk about.

11:15.421 --> 11:17.920
I'm not going to mince words.

11:17.921 --> 11:21.090
There's a void here today.

11:21.091 --> 11:22.880
We all feel it.

11:22.881 --> 11:25.840
We're all stunned and confused.

11:25.841 --> 11:27.260
In all that confusion,

11:27.261 --> 11:31.340
let's not forget about
what's really important...

11:31.341 --> 11:34.421
Troy, and all that he gave.

11:36.131 --> 11:40.131
Ann? Would you like to say a few words?

11:48.801 --> 11:51.170
Um...

11:51.171 --> 11:54.920
John and I have, um, been
around the block a few times.

11:54.921 --> 11:56.420
We're at that age

11:56.421 --> 11:58.460
where we're losing some
of our dearest friends,

11:58.461 --> 12:00.761
people we've known all our lives.

12:02.461 --> 12:05.920
But so many of you are so young.

12:05.921 --> 12:07.840
I can tell by looking around this room

12:07.841 --> 12:11.551
that this is the first
tragic death you've faced.

12:14.011 --> 12:17.260
I remember when I was told

12:17.261 --> 12:19.380
that my husband and
daughter were killed.

12:19.381 --> 12:22.261
I was... I was 20.

12:23.301 --> 12:25.761
My whole world fell down.

12:28.011 --> 12:31.011
The only thing that got
me through that...

12:33.421 --> 12:36.840
was people reaching out.

12:36.841 --> 12:40.340
That's the only way we get
through times like these.

12:40.341 --> 12:44.510
Compassion heals...

12:44.511 --> 12:46.551
all suffering.

12:50.841 --> 12:54.090
You never fail to surprise me.

12:54.091 --> 12:58.960
We've seen a lot of people
come and go over the years.

12:58.961 --> 13:01.050
Nature of the beast.

13:01.051 --> 13:02.421
Pardon the pun.

13:03.841 --> 13:06.220
But you and I are still here.

13:06.221 --> 13:09.261
Perhaps we'll be the last ones standing.

13:12.551 --> 13:16.921
Damien said you left
this in his apartment.

13:22.091 --> 13:24.170
I had nothing to do with that.

13:24.171 --> 13:27.340
Things are reaching a critical point.

13:27.341 --> 13:30.260
We can't afford to fall
into separate camps.

13:30.261 --> 13:34.010
Perhaps we should get used
to sharing the stage.

13:34.011 --> 13:35.300
What are you proposing?

13:35.301 --> 13:36.645
You've got Damien.

13:36.732 --> 13:39.071
I have everything else in place.

13:39.072 --> 13:42.231
We need to work together,
not against each other.

13:42.232 --> 13:46.651
We need to trust each other.

13:46.652 --> 13:48.362
I couldn't agree more.

13:50.072 --> 13:53.232
♪♪

13:55.652 --> 13:57.731
Igor Reneus.

13:57.732 --> 13:59.901
You and Kelly Baptiste
paid him a visit. Why?

13:59.902 --> 14:01.902
She was doing research for an article.

14:03.192 --> 14:05.901
Around the same time that she died

14:05.902 --> 14:07.821
in her "accident"...

14:07.822 --> 14:10.031
right outside of your
apartment, I might add...

14:10.032 --> 14:12.942
he was mauled to death
by a pack of wild dogs.

14:14.942 --> 14:17.031
The cab driver who hit Hermon Saroyan?

14:17.032 --> 14:19.571
He swerved to avoid a wild dog.

14:19.572 --> 14:22.361
I don't know what you're
up to or how you do it,

14:22.362 --> 14:26.362
but you're puling some
really freaky shit.

14:27.732 --> 14:31.231
I may to be able to prove it,

14:31.232 --> 14:34.732
but I know you're responsible
for those deaths.

14:38.822 --> 14:40.901
Get up.

14:40.902 --> 14:42.232
Wanna show you somethin'.

14:44.232 --> 14:46.151
[Door opens]

14:46.152 --> 14:48.771
[Indistinct conversations]

14:48.772 --> 14:51.321
So last night, I'm walking
down the hall just like this,

14:51.322 --> 14:53.071
when out of nowhere, a Rottweiler...

14:53.072 --> 14:54.771
must've weighed 90 pounds...

14:54.772 --> 14:56.901
jumps on me, tries to take my arm off.

14:56.902 --> 14:59.731
Ooh. Careful. You don't
wanna walk into that,

14:59.732 --> 15:01.232
get it on your shoes.

15:03.652 --> 15:07.232
♪♪

15:08.772 --> 15:10.731
Can you believe it?

15:10.732 --> 15:12.941
I was in the E.R. till 3:00 a.m.

15:12.942 --> 15:14.901
22 stitches.

15:14.902 --> 15:18.941
They did say there was no, uh,
permanent nerve damage, though.

15:18.942 --> 15:20.651
The dog was not so lucky.

15:20.652 --> 15:22.571
[Lights clank and click]

15:22.572 --> 15:27.191
[Electricity humming]

15:27.192 --> 15:29.861
[Faint hiss]

15:29.862 --> 15:31.861
Well... what the hell?

15:31.862 --> 15:33.731
He was trying to kill me, so...

15:33.732 --> 15:34.942
I blew his head off.

15:36.982 --> 15:39.231
Good thing he didn't go for
my shooter hand, though.

15:39.232 --> 15:41.111
[Inhales deeply] I would've been gone.

15:41.112 --> 15:44.611
[Exhales deeply] Scary thing
about this hallway...

15:44.612 --> 15:47.111
there are no cameras.

15:47.112 --> 15:50.902
♪♪

16:02.732 --> 16:05.112
[Sighs deeply]

16:09.772 --> 16:10.981
Uhh!

16:10.982 --> 16:13.651
Oh, yeah. Come on, try something.

16:13.652 --> 16:15.732
Give me the chance.

16:18.822 --> 16:20.821
Leave me alone.

16:20.822 --> 16:23.071
That professor, your dog
attack, the taxi...

16:23.072 --> 16:25.611
nothing to do with me.

16:25.612 --> 16:27.861
Let me tell you how this plays
out with guys like you,

16:27.862 --> 16:29.821
how we handle it.

16:29.822 --> 16:34.071
Now, I know you're a piece of
shit, but I can't prove it.

16:34.072 --> 16:36.901
So I keep my eyes on you.

16:36.902 --> 16:39.231
Person of interest.

16:39.232 --> 16:42.151
And I keep you here all
night for questioning,

16:42.152 --> 16:44.151
kick you free when you're exhausted,

16:44.152 --> 16:46.191
and then bring you back tomorrow...

16:46.192 --> 16:49.271
and the next night, and all next week.

16:49.272 --> 16:53.271
After a while, you've got a shadow.

16:53.272 --> 16:56.231
Always right over your shoulder.

16:56.232 --> 16:59.771
One night, you're driving.

16:59.772 --> 17:02.691
There's sirens in the mirror. Pull over.

17:02.692 --> 17:06.570
Busted tail light, expired tags. Mm.

17:06.571 --> 17:09.651
I'll find somethin'.

17:09.652 --> 17:13.570
And you're pissed 'cause
I'm crawling up your ass.

17:13.571 --> 17:16.401
Agitated.

17:16.402 --> 17:19.151
And I ask to see your license,

17:19.152 --> 17:23.112
and you reach over to get your wallet.

17:24.571 --> 17:26.771
Boom!

17:26.771 --> 17:28.570
[Chuckles]

17:28.571 --> 17:32.571
Just... I thought I saw a gun.

17:32.572 --> 17:34.231
I feared for my own life.

17:34.232 --> 17:39.732
But <i> you,</i> no one will miss
an asshole like you.

17:41.862 --> 17:43.322
Trust me...

17:45.822 --> 17:47.732
you don't want to do that.

17:49.772 --> 17:51.902
Are you threatening me?

17:53.982 --> 17:56.981
People who come after me,
they don't fare so well.

17:56.982 --> 17:58.731
You've seen enough to know.

17:58.732 --> 18:04.111
<i>Very</i> weird stuff happens around me.

18:04.112 --> 18:08.191
Not <i> to</i> me. Never to me. To others.

18:08.192 --> 18:10.771
Can't explain it.

18:10.772 --> 18:12.651
You think my wallet's a gun?

18:12.652 --> 18:15.031
Your pistol's likely to
blow up in your face.

18:15.032 --> 18:17.771
So you're the roadrunner,
and I'm the coyote?

18:17.772 --> 18:19.071
Is that what this is?

18:19.072 --> 18:20.321
I'm just a guy living his life,

18:20.322 --> 18:22.031
and you're just a weak-ass cop

18:22.032 --> 18:24.232
with nothing but a handful of piss.

18:28.192 --> 18:30.231
I'm a war photographer, remember?

18:30.232 --> 18:31.902
Mm-hmm.

18:33.072 --> 18:36.691
I've been in the shit.

18:36.692 --> 18:41.231
More than you ever will.

18:41.232 --> 18:44.611
You wanna play the cowboy?
Go ahead, pull your gun.

18:44.612 --> 18:48.232
♪♪

18:55.942 --> 18:59.271
Yeah.

18:59.272 --> 19:01.152
I didn't think so.

19:03.032 --> 19:04.362
[Pats arm]

19:05.732 --> 19:07.191
Hey, Sherlock Holmes,

19:07.192 --> 19:09.191
you know who seems to
have all the answers?

19:09.192 --> 19:10.981
Ann Rutledge.

19:10.982 --> 19:14.361
She has a room full of
my childhood possessions

19:14.362 --> 19:15.941
in her house,

19:15.942 --> 19:18.031
behind a secret doorway in a bookcase.

19:18.032 --> 19:23.691
Oh, so she's creating all these
deaths to make you look guilty?

19:23.692 --> 19:26.111
You're the police. You figure it out.

19:26.112 --> 19:28.071
[Phones ringing]

19:28.072 --> 19:32.611
[Indistinct conversations,
police radio chatter]

19:32.612 --> 19:35.111
[Conversations continue]

19:35.112 --> 19:36.771
What's he doing here?

19:36.772 --> 19:39.071
[Whispers loudly] The Destroyer!

19:39.072 --> 19:41.571
You let him in?!

19:41.572 --> 19:44.231
<i>He</i> is the one who
follows me in darkness.

19:44.232 --> 19:46.862
<i>He</i> is the serpent!

19:48.232 --> 19:50.071
He needs to stop running.

19:50.072 --> 19:53.151
It's time to confront this head on.

19:53.152 --> 19:54.731
What did you say?

19:54.732 --> 19:58.191
He urges me and tempts me.

19:58.192 --> 20:01.942
He is the lie!

20:03.072 --> 20:04.861
Hey!

20:04.862 --> 20:07.071
Uhh!

20:07.072 --> 20:09.731
[Grunting]

20:09.732 --> 20:11.612
- MAN: Hey! Hey! Hey! Hey!
- [Man shouting]

20:11.615 --> 20:13.612
- That's enough!
- Hey! Don't!

20:13.615 --> 20:14.942
- Get off!
- [Man whimpering]

20:14.945 --> 20:17.611
Get down! Hands behind your back!

20:17.612 --> 20:20.111
Hey! Don't! Don't! Don't! Hey, watch...

20:20.112 --> 20:21.172
Uhh!

20:21.173 --> 20:22.231
[Women screaming]

20:22.232 --> 20:23.752
[Stabbing]

20:23.753 --> 20:25.271
Uhh! Uhh! Uhh!

20:25.272 --> 20:27.901
[Whimpering]

20:27.902 --> 20:28.902
[Scissors clatter]

20:28.903 --> 20:29.902
[Grunts]

20:29.903 --> 20:31.231
[Screaming, gasping]

20:31.232 --> 20:32.901
MAN: [Shouts indistinctly]
Get him up here!

20:32.902 --> 20:35.652
[Gasping, clamoring]

20:38.272 --> 20:41.031
[Screaming continues]

20:41.032 --> 20:44.071
[Clamoring continues]

20:44.072 --> 20:46.151
The Beast.

20:46.152 --> 20:51.071
♪♪

20:52.599 --> 20:55.997
Mr. Thorn's work is brilliant.

20:56.022 --> 20:58.481
There's no question about that.

20:58.482 --> 21:03.521
But we do have some concerns
about him professionally.

21:03.522 --> 21:07.482
Is this because he didn't
show up to the interview?

21:09.442 --> 21:12.231
[Sighs] Among other things.

21:12.232 --> 21:13.442
[Scoffs]

21:16.272 --> 21:20.481
The woman he loves
dies a horrible death,

21:20.482 --> 21:23.601
is literally ripped from his hands,

21:23.602 --> 21:25.441
and you think he should've
made this his priority?

21:25.442 --> 21:28.731
Two days after Kelly dies,
he risks his own life

21:28.732 --> 21:32.151
to save a stranger's kid
from the train tracks,

21:32.152 --> 21:34.101
and you're saying he's
not a reliable guy?

21:34.102 --> 21:35.441
Mr. Golkar...

21:35.442 --> 21:37.271
Damien Thorn is the best
photographer out there,

21:37.272 --> 21:38.481
hands down.

21:38.482 --> 21:40.061
But he's also the most selfless,

21:40.062 --> 21:42.101
courageous guy I've ever met.

21:42.102 --> 21:45.481
And if these aren't the
qualities you want

21:45.482 --> 21:47.441
in your collective,

21:47.442 --> 21:48.652
then good luck to you.

21:52.482 --> 21:55.602
Mr. Golkar, please, wait.

22:01.062 --> 22:02.732
[Doorbell rings]

22:07.272 --> 22:09.061
[Door creaks]

22:09.062 --> 22:10.561
Detective Shay.

22:10.562 --> 22:12.651
Good afternoon, Ms. Rutledge.

22:12.652 --> 22:14.401
Is something wrong? Is Damien...

22:14.402 --> 22:17.481
No, he's fine. Do you,
uh, mind if I come in?

22:17.482 --> 22:19.312
- [Clock chiming in distance]
- Of course.

22:19.315 --> 22:22.022
- Just had a few questions to ask you.
- [Door closes]

22:22.025 --> 22:23.731
May I offer you some coffee?

22:23.732 --> 22:25.691
No, thank you.

22:25.692 --> 22:27.311
I'm gonna get right to the point.

22:27.312 --> 22:29.151
Mr. Thorn's down at the
police station right now.

22:29.152 --> 22:30.941
We brought him in for questioning

22:30.942 --> 22:34.061
about his possible involvement
in the death of Troy Hendrie.

22:34.062 --> 22:36.601
Mr. Thorn suggested that
you might've known him.

22:36.602 --> 22:40.061
Yes. He worked with me at Armitage.

22:40.062 --> 22:41.521
Hmm.

22:41.522 --> 22:43.271
Ms. Rutledge, are you Mr.
Thorn's attorney?

22:43.272 --> 22:44.981
Yes.

22:44.982 --> 22:46.441
He says you're not.

22:46.442 --> 22:48.561
He says he only met you a week ago,

22:48.562 --> 22:51.101
and he suggested that you
might be stalking him.

22:51.102 --> 22:54.021
[Scoffs] He said that?

22:54.022 --> 22:57.021
Well, to be specific, I'm
not his personal attorney.

22:57.022 --> 22:58.981
I represent the Thorn Family Estate.

22:58.982 --> 23:01.101
Hmm.

23:01.102 --> 23:04.601
He said there was a special
room in your house,

23:04.602 --> 23:07.101
with, uh, his personal belongings

23:07.102 --> 23:09.061
from when he was a child?

23:09.062 --> 23:10.521
Now that's ridiculous.

23:10.522 --> 23:12.401
Well, he said this room has access

23:12.402 --> 23:15.152
through a secret doorway in a bookshelf.

23:24.692 --> 23:27.272
[Doors creak]

23:35.272 --> 23:36.601
[Exhales]

23:36.602 --> 23:39.151
It's a panic room.

23:39.152 --> 23:41.941
I never use it.

23:41.942 --> 23:43.522
I never panic.

23:47.982 --> 23:49.982
[Footsteps echo]

23:56.062 --> 23:58.271
I suppose I should warn you.

23:58.272 --> 24:01.311
Damien's given to very erratic behavior.

24:01.312 --> 24:06.941
♪♪

24:06.942 --> 24:10.731
<i>[Eerie whispering]</i>

24:10.732 --> 24:13.231
Are you saying that he's a liar?

24:13.232 --> 24:17.231
♪♪

24:17.232 --> 24:19.482
[Switch clicks]

24:22.482 --> 24:24.601
I'm saying he has trouble distinguishing

24:24.602 --> 24:28.191
between reality and fantasy.

24:28.192 --> 24:29.442
[Exhales]

24:32.602 --> 24:34.102
[Exhales]

24:49.482 --> 24:53.061
[Footsteps approach]

24:53.062 --> 24:54.601
[Clears throat]

24:54.602 --> 24:57.231
[Elevator whirring]

24:57.232 --> 24:59.521
Good meeting?

24:59.522 --> 25:01.102
You have that look.

25:02.652 --> 25:04.522
I think I got their attention.

25:06.232 --> 25:09.271
Who were you pitching? Bob? Carol?

25:09.272 --> 25:11.231
That fat bastard Luigi?

25:11.232 --> 25:12.521
[Both chuckle]

25:12.522 --> 25:15.651
No, it was, uh, Fumika.

25:15.652 --> 25:19.601
Ooh. Fumika... she's tough.

25:19.602 --> 25:23.021
I heard she once knocked out
an intern with a staple gun.

25:23.022 --> 25:24.442
Don't tell her I told you.

25:25.602 --> 25:27.941
[Chuckles]

25:27.942 --> 25:30.731
I hope you're headed out to celebrate.

25:30.732 --> 25:34.271
Yeah, you know what? I <i> am</i>
heading out to celebrate.

25:34.272 --> 25:36.191
Know any good bars around here?

25:36.192 --> 25:38.601
♪♪

25:38.602 --> 25:41.191
ANN: I've known him his entire life.

25:41.192 --> 25:43.941
Besides handling the legal
affairs of the Thorn Estate,

25:43.942 --> 25:47.191
I'm also executor of his father's will.

25:47.192 --> 25:50.021
Then why would Damien claim to
only have met you last week?

25:50.022 --> 25:51.481
He spent years overseas

25:51.482 --> 25:54.481
in extremely high pressure situations.

25:54.482 --> 25:57.441
That's certainly taken a psychic toll.

25:57.442 --> 25:58.941
Could you be more specific?

25:58.942 --> 26:00.561
The specifics of his mental health...

26:00.562 --> 26:02.272
- [Pours liquid]
- ...are attorney-client privilege.

26:02.275 --> 26:04.401
But you have to understand,

26:04.402 --> 26:07.191
if there's a hell on earth,

26:07.192 --> 26:10.101
Damien's been dead center,
photographing it.

26:10.102 --> 26:12.311
Mm.

26:12.312 --> 26:14.231
Does he own dogs?

26:14.232 --> 26:16.151
I don't think so.

26:16.152 --> 26:18.441
'Cause I was attacked by one last night.

26:18.442 --> 26:20.771
Another man was mauled to
death by a pack of them.

26:20.772 --> 26:23.601
[Chuckles] Damien training
dogs to attack people?

26:23.602 --> 26:26.691
You give him too much credit.

26:26.692 --> 26:30.941
I will say he used to, uh,
be prone to fits of rage.

26:30.942 --> 26:32.601
He supposedly knocked his
mother over a balcony

26:32.602 --> 26:34.101
when he was young.

26:34.102 --> 26:36.191
I assumed it was an accident.

26:36.192 --> 26:38.481
But then I was on the board of
one of the school he attended,

26:38.482 --> 26:41.101
and there was an altercation
with another student.

26:41.102 --> 26:42.167
I can't remember his name.

26:42.168 --> 26:43.231
Thorn hurt him?

26:43.232 --> 26:46.191
[Sighs] The poor boy spent
his life in a facility.

26:46.192 --> 26:48.981
So he rang his bell pretty bad?

26:48.982 --> 26:50.651
Charles Powell. That's the name.

26:50.652 --> 26:53.231
[Clicks pen]

26:53.232 --> 26:54.521
I will look into that.

26:54.522 --> 26:57.101
Damien was treated after that.

26:57.102 --> 27:00.271
And I thought he'd
pulled himself together.

27:00.272 --> 27:03.101
But I guess we can only outrun
our demons for so long.

27:03.102 --> 27:05.102
Wouldn't you agree, Detective?

27:07.272 --> 27:08.792
[Objects rattling]

27:08.793 --> 27:10.311
<i>[TV playing indistinctly]</i>

27:10.312 --> 27:11.561
[Siren wailing in distance]

27:11.562 --> 27:13.271
[Door creaks]

27:13.272 --> 27:14.652
- [Speaks Yoruba]
- [Objects clatter]

27:14.655 --> 27:16.101
What the hell is this?

27:16.102 --> 27:18.271
He's a very powerful <i> babalawo.</i>

27:18.272 --> 27:19.521
A witch doctor?

27:19.522 --> 27:21.311
The bird in the tub was Kelly.

27:21.312 --> 27:23.061
The bird that broke the
stained glass window

27:23.062 --> 27:24.561
at the funeral, it was Kelly.

27:24.562 --> 27:27.401
She's trying to come back
or she's lost her way.

27:27.402 --> 27:29.101
Either way, she's trying
to tell us something.

27:29.102 --> 27:30.397
He can help her.

27:30.398 --> 27:31.691
[Squawks]

27:31.692 --> 27:33.361
[Whispers] Mom, this is not real.

27:33.362 --> 27:35.441
This is an old world superstition.

27:35.442 --> 27:37.361
You can't possibly believe this.

27:37.362 --> 27:41.271
You found a... bird in your bath?

27:41.272 --> 27:44.101
[Clucking]

27:44.102 --> 27:45.311
Yes.

27:45.312 --> 27:47.271
Then you are threatened, too.

27:47.272 --> 27:49.981
The spirits will come for you.

27:49.982 --> 27:53.941
[Rooster continues clucking]

27:53.942 --> 27:57.562
[Speaks Yoruba]

27:59.102 --> 28:00.602
What are you gonna do?

28:09.692 --> 28:13.441
This house need to be purified.

28:13.442 --> 28:14.547
[Continues plucking]

28:14.548 --> 28:15.651
[Whispers] Mom.

28:15.652 --> 28:18.441
[Normal voice] Oh, my God. Please stop.

28:18.442 --> 28:19.942
[Scratches]

28:19.943 --> 28:21.442
[Speaks Yoruba]

28:25.102 --> 28:27.021
No. No! Those are Kelly's things!

28:27.022 --> 28:30.101
Please! No! Oh, no! No!

28:30.102 --> 28:32.061
[Squishing]

28:32.062 --> 28:35.481
May the road be open to you.

28:35.482 --> 28:40.191
May nothing evil meet you on the way.

28:40.192 --> 28:42.442
[Squish, blood continues dripping]

28:48.522 --> 28:50.272
[Slices, thud]

28:52.312 --> 28:55.062
[Blood continues dripping]

28:56.602 --> 28:57.982
[Thud]

29:01.272 --> 29:03.522
[Whoosh]

29:05.272 --> 29:09.982
♪♪

29:13.602 --> 29:17.101
[Loud whoosh]

29:17.102 --> 29:18.481
♪♪

29:18.482 --> 29:20.402
[Rumbling]

29:32.482 --> 29:37.402
♪♪

29:46.152 --> 29:49.442
♪♪

29:52.841 --> 29:54.573
I hate photography.

29:54.660 --> 29:56.707
Taking pictures is for people
who can't remember things

29:56.732 --> 29:58.441
with their own brain.

29:58.442 --> 30:01.021
[Laughs] Kidding.

30:01.022 --> 30:02.441
These are great, really.

30:02.442 --> 30:05.191
I'm not surprised you crushed it today.

30:05.192 --> 30:07.021
♪♪

30:07.022 --> 30:09.271
So you and this photographer
been working together long?

30:09.272 --> 30:10.611
Uh, two years.

30:10.612 --> 30:12.611
You know, I think we make a-a good team.

30:12.612 --> 30:14.941
You guys have obviously
been through a lot.

30:14.942 --> 30:16.612
You don't even know.

30:17.982 --> 30:20.151
So tell me.

30:20.152 --> 30:22.941
All right. Uh, well, uh,

30:22.942 --> 30:25.321
I was working as a
translator in, uh, Libya

30:25.322 --> 30:27.904
for the Americans, and, um,

30:28.022 --> 30:30.061
Gadaffi loyalists, they just
blitzed through Tripoli,

30:30.062 --> 30:31.521
and they were rounding people up.

30:31.522 --> 30:33.271
And, you know, they put me in a ditch

30:33.272 --> 30:34.931
with a hood over my head.

30:34.932 --> 30:39.021
And the soldiers, they
moved down the line.

30:39.022 --> 30:43.271
Started, uh, shooting
guys I knew one by one.

30:43.272 --> 30:46.181
And, uh, all I could think about w...

30:46.182 --> 30:49.601
was my mother, my sisters.

30:49.602 --> 30:53.891
They'd, uh, never know
what happened to me.

30:53.892 --> 30:55.931
♪♪

30:55.932 --> 30:59.601
And Damien, he just steps
up out of nowhere.

30:59.602 --> 31:02.312
And I have no idea what he said, but...

31:05.102 --> 31:06.891
...they let me go.

31:06.892 --> 31:10.182
♪♪

31:12.522 --> 31:15.851
Never really told anyone
that story before.

31:15.852 --> 31:17.852
Why are you telling it now?

31:19.562 --> 31:22.931
I don't know.

31:22.932 --> 31:24.471
Taxi!

31:24.472 --> 31:25.472
[Both laughing]

31:25.473 --> 31:26.472
Ooh, hoo!

31:26.473 --> 31:28.142
- All right, no, I got it. I got this.
- [Horn blares]

31:28.145 --> 31:29.352
- Yo! Wait!
- Oh, he sped up!

31:29.355 --> 31:30.372
Oh, come on! Taxi!

31:30.373 --> 31:31.391
[Laughing]

31:31.392 --> 31:33.181
Seriously! Wow. Don't worry, I got it.

31:33.182 --> 31:34.391
This is it for sure.

31:34.392 --> 31:36.062
Oh.

31:37.852 --> 31:40.181
Wow.

31:40.182 --> 31:41.521
You wanna give it a go?

31:41.522 --> 31:44.231
[Laughs]

31:44.232 --> 31:46.182
[Horn honks in distance]

31:56.432 --> 32:00.022
You gotta teach me that trick sometime.

32:04.522 --> 32:06.522
[Whispers] Right.

32:07.432 --> 32:09.022
[Brakes squeal]

32:22.852 --> 32:24.352
Bye.

32:32.022 --> 32:33.852
[Door opens]

32:35.602 --> 32:37.931
[Door closes]

32:37.932 --> 32:41.101
[Exhales] We can't hold you.

32:41.102 --> 32:42.522
You're free to go.

32:46.142 --> 32:49.561
[Indistinct conversations]

32:49.562 --> 32:52.852
[Police radio chatter]

32:54.642 --> 32:56.892
♪♪

32:59.022 --> 33:00.181
What is this?

33:00.182 --> 33:02.181
Did you see the room?

33:02.182 --> 33:03.891
I'll take it from here.

33:03.892 --> 33:07.471
Everything's going to be all right.

33:07.472 --> 33:10.141
What the hell did she tell you?
You can't let her do this.

33:10.142 --> 33:11.391
You take care.

33:11.392 --> 33:13.101
And don't let me see you again.

33:13.102 --> 33:14.392
Let's get you home.

33:20.272 --> 33:22.101
What did you say to him?

33:22.102 --> 33:24.391
That you've witnessed more than
your fair share of suffering.

33:24.392 --> 33:27.391
Did you tell him the part you've played?

33:27.392 --> 33:30.061
Not exactly the most eloquent
"thank you" I've ever received.

33:30.062 --> 33:31.931
Why would I say thank you?

33:31.932 --> 33:33.141
You say you've been there my whole life,

33:33.142 --> 33:34.352
- watching out for me.
- I have.

33:34.355 --> 33:36.181
You've done a shitty job!

33:36.182 --> 33:39.311
Look at this mess! You want gratitude?

33:39.312 --> 33:43.231
I can't leave my apartment
without shit going down.

33:43.232 --> 33:45.521
Enough death.

33:45.522 --> 33:47.471
You're just looking
for someone to blame.

33:47.472 --> 33:48.891
[Siren wailing in distance]

33:48.892 --> 33:50.561
Oh, you're not the puppet master?

33:50.562 --> 33:52.231
Oh, you sure do play the part well.

33:52.232 --> 33:54.352
The part I play is insignificant.

33:55.562 --> 33:58.101
[Indistinct conversations]

33:58.102 --> 34:03.641
<i>This</i> stops now. These
killings will stop now.

34:03.642 --> 34:07.022
Even if I have to slit
your throat to make them.

34:09.681 --> 34:11.022
Do it.

34:14.022 --> 34:16.521
Slit my throat.

34:16.522 --> 34:19.021
You know that's what you want.

34:19.022 --> 34:22.522
Desperate men have nothing to lose.

34:28.472 --> 34:32.851
♪♪

34:37.891 --> 34:40.061
The day will come.

34:40.062 --> 34:43.851
♪♪

34:50.945 --> 34:53.034
[Indistinct conversations,
phone ringing]

34:57.835 --> 35:00.244
Did you go to Ann Rutledge's home today?

35:00.245 --> 35:01.784
I hear you accused her

35:01.785 --> 35:03.675
of being involved in
that escalator death.

35:03.722 --> 35:04.555
N-Not exactly...

35:04.580 --> 35:07.053
I don't give a rat's ass
what you were doing. Stop it.

35:07.055 --> 35:08.841
Captain, listen, I went
there for a reason.

35:08.842 --> 35:10.091
Damien Thorn, he accused her of...

35:10.092 --> 35:12.301
What's your obsession with this guy?

35:12.302 --> 35:14.091
Is he your type?

35:14.092 --> 35:15.761
Just drop it.

35:15.762 --> 35:17.801
Let's not make this
another Baltimore, okay?

35:17.802 --> 35:19.801
Took you years to climb
out of that pile of shit.

35:19.802 --> 35:21.721
You wanna go right back there?
I don't think so.

35:21.722 --> 35:26.341
Be smart. Leave Thorn alone.

35:26.342 --> 35:28.011
[Air hisses]

35:28.012 --> 35:29.841
[Canister thuds, click]

35:29.842 --> 35:32.091
[Train whistle blows in distance]

35:32.092 --> 35:34.012
[Knock on door]

35:35.262 --> 35:38.341
[Door creaks]

35:38.342 --> 35:39.971
Hey.

35:39.972 --> 35:41.261
Can I come in?

35:41.262 --> 35:42.682
Of course.

35:45.012 --> 35:47.801
[Door creaks, closes]

35:47.802 --> 35:50.681
Everything all right?

35:50.682 --> 35:51.842
No.

35:59.682 --> 36:03.181
Where did you get this?

36:03.182 --> 36:04.921
[Voice breaks] Ever since Kelly died,

36:04.922 --> 36:07.261
I've been seeing things.

36:07.262 --> 36:10.681
The church where we held the funeral...

36:10.682 --> 36:14.011
you remember the bird that
flew into the window?

36:14.012 --> 36:16.721
I found another one in my drain.

36:16.722 --> 36:18.181
My mom's Nigerian.

36:18.182 --> 36:21.181
I told her, and she brought
in a Yoruba priest.

36:21.182 --> 36:25.052
He thinks Kelly's trying to talk to us.

36:26.262 --> 36:28.131
That was a scam.

36:28.132 --> 36:31.761
What else could it be?

36:31.762 --> 36:35.131
There's a rational
explanation for all of this.

36:35.132 --> 36:38.421
You know, a bird flew into your window,

36:38.422 --> 36:40.381
and another got caught in your drain.

36:40.382 --> 36:44.261
I don't know how, but it did.

36:44.262 --> 36:47.341
And your fortune-teller
pulled a magic trick.

36:47.342 --> 36:49.472
He might as well have
sawed a lady in half.

36:54.922 --> 36:57.342
I wish things were different.

36:59.182 --> 37:02.301
But trust me, I do.

37:02.302 --> 37:06.801
The things I... and Kelly...
have seen...

37:06.802 --> 37:09.381
brutality, natural
disasters, massacres...

37:09.382 --> 37:12.051
there's always the ones left behind.

37:12.052 --> 37:13.972
Human wreckage.

37:16.682 --> 37:19.841
People suffering so badly,

37:19.842 --> 37:21.341
they can't possibly go on.

37:21.342 --> 37:23.472
They need answers. They're...

37:25.342 --> 37:29.301
Well, their... their pain is... is so...

37:29.302 --> 37:33.302
great, th-there must
be a higher purpose.

37:35.722 --> 37:37.182
There must be a reason.

37:41.785 --> 37:43.655
But, uh...

37:45.379 --> 37:46.839
There is none.

37:49.749 --> 37:51.629
Kelly died.

37:54.038 --> 37:56.298
And a bird is just a bird.

37:59.379 --> 38:01.038
[Exhales sharply]

38:01.039 --> 38:02.798
I'm sorry.

38:02.798 --> 38:05.457
[Inhales sharply] I'm...

38:05.459 --> 38:06.709
- No...
- [Sighs deeply]

38:06.712 --> 38:08.458
I am.

38:08.459 --> 38:10.999
You know, I wish you two
had gotten to be together.

38:12.629 --> 38:14.878
She really loved you.

38:14.879 --> 38:16.628
I probably shouldn't be saying that.

38:16.629 --> 38:18.998
No, it's okay.

38:18.999 --> 38:20.669
I know.

38:27.299 --> 38:30.128
[Door opens]

38:30.128 --> 38:31.628
[Door closes]

38:35.339 --> 38:37.799
♪♪

38:51.089 --> 38:52.588
[Notebook clatters]

38:53.175 --> 38:53.708
[Imitating airplane engine]

38:53.733 --> 38:55.868
You don't think McGarry's
gonna make trouble?

38:55.893 --> 38:57.179
He hates you, you know.

38:57.534 --> 38:59.203
He hates everybody.
That's why he's a cop.

38:59.228 --> 39:00.727
Well, he's right. You should
leave well enough alone.

39:01.322 --> 39:03.321
I got it.

39:03.322 --> 39:05.981
If that suspect has a history
of mental illness...

39:05.982 --> 39:07.901
That only confuses his alibi.

39:07.902 --> 39:09.731
That doesn't explain anything
about all the deaths around him.

39:09.732 --> 39:11.061
PATRICK: It's a statistical cluster...

39:11.062 --> 39:12.771
Don't talk down to me, okay?

39:12.772 --> 39:14.861
You know I can't handle
the Stephen Hawking shit.

39:14.862 --> 39:16.441
Well, I try not to talk down to you.

39:16.442 --> 39:17.771
It's just so hard not to.

39:17.772 --> 39:19.151
[Chuckles]

39:19.152 --> 39:21.021
♪♪

39:21.022 --> 39:22.441
JAMES: Are we getting all healthy now?

39:22.442 --> 39:23.981
PATRICK: Yeah, we're
gonna go with olive oil.

39:23.982 --> 39:25.731
JAMES: Olive oil. So domestic.
I love this.

39:25.732 --> 39:28.441
[Conversation continues indistinctly]

39:28.442 --> 39:30.482
- JAMES: That's it. See that?
- PATRICK: Parsley, yeah.

39:30.485 --> 39:32.271
JAMES: How many eggs do you want?

39:32.272 --> 39:34.061
PATRICK: Two.

39:34.062 --> 39:35.901
This Thorn guy is a dick.

39:35.902 --> 39:37.521
He walks into my station,

39:37.522 --> 39:39.151
and there's some guy in
there for parking tickets

39:39.152 --> 39:41.061
who suddenly decides he
wants to castrate himself.

39:41.062 --> 39:43.151
And then there's all these
deaths and the dog attack.

39:43.152 --> 39:44.771
I-I just don't get it.

39:44.772 --> 39:46.151
You're not gonna leave
well enough alone, are ya?

39:46.276 --> 39:48.145
I try, but it's just so hard not to.

39:48.146 --> 39:49.945
[Chuckles]

39:49.946 --> 39:52.895
♪♪

39:52.896 --> 39:56.275
[Water rippling]

39:56.276 --> 40:00.395
♪♪

40:00.396 --> 40:02.396
[Birds chirping]

40:09.646 --> 40:13.355
[Water splashing]

40:13.356 --> 40:15.646
PATRICK: Jacob! Breakfast!

40:17.026 --> 40:19.315
Babe, come on. It'll get cold.

40:19.316 --> 40:21.356
Jacob!

40:25.236 --> 40:30.236
♪♪

40:39.486 --> 40:43.525
♪♪

40:43.526 --> 40:45.895
Jacob! Jacob!

40:45.896 --> 40:49.526
♪♪

41:10.356 --> 41:14.066
<i>[Roars]</i>

41:15.446 --> 41:18.026
♪♪

41:30.856 --> 41:32.566
Oh, God, Jacob.

41:36.526 --> 41:38.895
Patrick! Patrick!

41:38.896 --> 41:40.066
- Jacob?
- <i>[Growls]</i>

41:40.069 --> 41:41.395
I'm here. I got him. I got him.

41:41.396 --> 41:43.025
All right, Jacob. Jacob.

41:43.026 --> 41:45.106
- Oh, Jacob.
- Honey, come on. Jacob, wake up.

41:45.107 --> 41:46.395
He's not breathing. He's not breathing.

41:46.396 --> 41:48.065
Move out of the way. Move
out of the way. 1, 2...

41:48.066 --> 41:49.945
Come on. Come on.

41:49.946 --> 41:51.066
Come on, Jacob. Come on.

41:51.067 --> 41:52.185
[Coughs]

41:52.186 --> 41:53.855
Ah! There he goes! It's okay. It's okay.

41:53.856 --> 41:55.186
- [Whispers] Okay.
- It's okay. It's okay.

41:55.189 --> 41:57.985
[Grunts] Okay, get him in there.

41:57.986 --> 41:59.525
I got him. We need an ambulance.

41:59.526 --> 42:00.946
- You got him?
- Yeah.

42:00.949 --> 42:02.185
[Panting]

42:02.186 --> 42:04.235
<i>[Growls]</i>

42:04.236 --> 42:06.895
[Water rippling]

